'''Columbitech''', founded in 2000, provides [[wireless security]] to secure mobile devices,<ref name="Wall Street Journal">[https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB119717610996418467 "Lost Connections", ''Wall Street Journal'', December 11 2007].</ref> with support for [[Wireless LAN|WLAN]] and public networks, including [[3G]], [[4G]] and [[WiMAX]]. The company is headquartered in [[Stockholm, Sweden]] with offices in [[New York City]].
==Columbitech Mobile VPN== The Columbitech [[Mobile Virtual Private Network (Mobile VPN)|mobile VPN]] provides remote network access to field mobility users, corporate WLAN users and telecommuters – mobilizing the enterprise.<ref name="Mobile Enterprise">[http://www.mobileenterprisemag.com/ME2/dirmod.asp?sid=&nm=&type=Publishing&mod=Publications%3A%3AArticle&mid=8F3A7027421841978F18BE895F87F791&tier=4&id=D7B7F1A7229743C1A55EFC1BD55DF05F "Mobile VPN for the Field", ''Mobile Enterprise'', February 2008].</ref> The solution is encrypted on standards-based [[Wireless Transport Layer Security]] (WTLS) and holds a [[FIPS 140-2]] certification.
The technology is utilized in the retail industry to meet [[PCI DSS]] requirements,<ref name="Stores Magazine">[http://www.stores.org/LPinformation_new/2008/05/LPiEdit2.asp "LINUX-based VPN system has NEXCOM running a tight ship", ''Stores Magazine'', May 2008] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080518005119/http://www.stores.org/LPinformation_new/2008/05/LPiEdit2.asp |date=2008-05-18 }}.</ref> and in other industries where mobile devices are used over wireless networks.
